mastics of the ancient Christians of Catania (see Korhonen 2004: 80): for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεόδουλος\u003C/span> see IMusCatania 183 l. 4 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001361\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001361\u003C/a>, IG 14, no. 538 l. 3 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001357\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001357\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Ferrua interprets the inscription differently and suggests the following integration at ll. 1-2 \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεο|[δοσίου Αὐγ. τὸ β´] κὲ Μαξιμου λα[μπρ. ἀνδρὸς τὸ β´]\u003C/span>. The inscription would mention the consuls for the year 388 CE, Theodosius, the Eastern Roman emperor, and not Flavius Merobaudes, the other consul in that year, but Maximus, who usurped the Western throne. According to Ferrua (1982-1983: 8), he was mentioned in the inscription \"in una specie di compromesso\" as a private man (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">λαμπρὸς ἀνήρ\u003C/span> and not \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Αὔγουστος\u003C/span>). The dating would therefore be the first part of the year (January/February?) of 388 CE since Maximus died in August of that year. Nevertheless, Ferrua’s integration seems arbitrary, since the fragment seems intact on the right.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":216,"html":217},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 36.0839 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 1962.0389 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1961 196 fig. 21 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001852\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001852\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1982-1983 7 no. 15 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001996\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001996\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Kajanto 1965 276 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002342\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002342\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 80 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":219,"html":220},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[222,224],{"image":93,"thumb":223,"title":96},"ISic003006_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":225,"thumb":226,"title":96},"ISic003006.jpg","ISic003006-thumb.jpg","\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Christian (?) epitaph\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu